JO  - Econometrica
JA  - Econometrica
SP  - 651
EP  - 691
VL  - 83
IS  - 2
KW  - Recursive choice
KW  - stochastic choice
KW  - preference for flexibility
KW  - preference for delay
PB  - John Wiley & Sons, Ltd
SN  - 0012-9682
UR  - https://doi.org/10.3982/ECTA11846
Y2  - 2024/03/26
N2  - We characterize a generalization of discounted logistic choice that incorporates a parameter to capture different views the agent might have about the costs and benefits of larger choice sets. The discounted logit model used in the empirical literature is the special case that displays a ?preference for flexibility? in the sense that the agent always prefers to add additional items to a menu. Other cases display varying levels of ?choice aversion,? where the agent prefers to remove items from a menu if their ex ante value is below a threshold. We show that higher choice aversion, as measured by dislike of bigger menus, also corresponds to an increased preference for putting off decisions as late as possible.
ER  - 

